[Podman](https://podman.io/) is a daemonless container engine with a mostly Docker-compatible command line interface.  It can be used with TRAMP by customising `docker-tramp-docker-executable` to `podman`.

Merge pull request #5 from legoscia/ignore-docker-ps-errors

Ignore errors when collecting names for completion

Ignore errors when collecting names for completion

If the Docker container you want to access is on a remote machine (using
Tramp's multi-hop syntax, e.g. /ssh:user@host|docker:abc123:), but the
local machine doesn't have the "docker" binary, then completion would
signal an error, which would abort the minibuffer prompt when opening a
file.

With this change, errors from "docker ps" are silently ignored, thus
enabling the use of remote Docker containers, though without name
completion.
Add option to access with container names
Change docker method to use sh instead of bash
Rename docker.el to docker-tramp.el
Initial import
